{
  "local_port": 51030,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I want to activate my old whatsapp but I'm over seas and have the old number?",
  "response": "Activating your old WhatsApp account while overseas is possible as long as you can receive the verification code on your old phone number. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you through the process:\n\n### **1. Ensure You Have Access to Your Old Number**\n- **SIM Card Active:** Make sure your old SIM card is active and inserted into a device that can receive SMS or calls. If you\u2019re traveling abroad, ensure that international roaming is enabled on your SIM to receive messages or calls.\n- **Roaming Services:** Contact your mobile carrier beforehand to confirm that roaming services are active. This will help prevent issues with receiving the verification code.\n\n### **2. Install WhatsApp on Your Device**\n- **Download the App:** If you haven't already, download and install the latest version of WhatsApp from the [Apple App Store](https://apps.apple.com/app/whatsapp-messenger/id310633997) or [Google Play Store](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.whatsapp&hl=en&gl=US).\n\n### **3. Begin the Verification Process**\n- **Open WhatsApp:** Launch the app and tap on **\"Agree and Continue\"** to accept the terms of service.\n- **Enter Your Old Number:** When prompted, enter your old phone number, including the country code (e.g., +1 for the USA).\n\n### **4. Receive the Verification Code**\n- **Automatic SMS Verification:** WhatsApp will attempt to verify your number by sending an SMS with a 6-digit code. If your phone can receive international SMS:\n  - **Wait for the Code:** It usually arrives within a few minutes.\n  - **Enter the Code:** Input the code into WhatsApp to complete verification.\n  \n- **If SMS Doesn't Arrive:**\n  - **Choose \"Call Me\":** If the SMS doesn't arrive within about an hour, tap on **\"Call me\"**. You will receive an automated voice call with the verification code.\n  - **Enter the Code:** Listen carefully to the code provided during the call and enter it into WhatsApp.\n\n### **5. Complete the Setup**\n- **Restore Backups (Optional):** If you have previously backed up your WhatsApp chats to iCloud (iPhone) or Google Drive (Android), you can choose to restore them during the setup process.\n- **Set Up Profile:** Enter your name and set a profile picture if prompted.\n\n### **6. Troubleshooting Tips**\n- **No SIM Access:** If you don\u2019t have access to the SIM card but can access SMS through another device or service (like a virtual phone number), make sure it can receive verification codes.\n- **Carrier Issues:** If you\u2019re unable to receive SMS or calls, contact your mobile carrier to ensure there are no restrictions or blocks on your number.\n- **WhatsApp Support:** If you've tried all the above steps and still can't activate WhatsApp, consider reaching out to [WhatsApp Support](https://www.whatsapp.com/contact/) for further assistance.\n\n### **Additional Recommendations**\n- **Keep Your SIM Active:** Even if you're traveling, keeping your SIM active ensures you can receive important messages, including WhatsApp verification codes.\n- **Update Your Contact Information:** If you plan to switch to a new number in the future, use WhatsApp\u2019s **Change Number** feature to update your contact details without losing your chat history.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to successfully activate your old WhatsApp account while overseas. If you encounter any issues, don't hesitate to seek assistance from WhatsApp Support or your mobile carrier.",
